and I need to keep the lights on, so--

31:39.022 --> 31:41.858
-I don't like other guys touching you.
-You don't control me, Rock.

31:41.941 --> 31:43.484
[Henry] Is there a problem here, Rock?

31:44.736 --> 31:46.279
No, there's no problem.

31:46.779 --> 31:48.031
[Noel clears throat]

31:48.448 --> 31:49.824
I hate to be forward,

31:49.908 --> 31:52.952
but would you like to join me
for a little slow dance inside?

31:53.328 --> 31:54.370
I'd love to.

32:00.543 --> 32:01.586
[knocking on door]

32:02.086 --> 32:03.880
-Oh, Ernie!
-Hiya, babe?

32:04.964 --> 32:06.591
[both chuckling]

32:07.425 --> 32:09.177
Where's, uh, Larry?

32:09.719 --> 32:11.304
Oh, I don't know. London?

32:11.846 --> 32:13.848
I'm afraid we've started to grow apart.

32:14.057 --> 32:17.268
He doesn't like my moods, and that doesn't
leave much of me to like, now does it?

32:17.352 --> 32:18.811
Oh, I'm sorry to hear that.

32:18.895 --> 32:21.898
I was hospitalized recently,
but I'm doing much better now.

32:22.273 --> 32:24.692
And I've got a great piece of material.

32:24.776 --> 32:29.739
Tenns wrote a magnificent play
called <i>A Streetcar Named Desire.</i>

32:29.822 --> 32:31.532
It's about to go up in London.

32:31.616 --> 32:33.993
The role is Blanche DuBois.

32:34.077 --> 32:37.372
In a lot of ways, she's another highly
strung Southern belle like Scarlett.

32:37.914 --> 32:40.208
Oh, that role threw me off the deep end
for two whole years.

32:40.291 --> 32:43.169
Can I, uh, ask what you're doing?

32:43.252 --> 32:45.838
I am organizing my bracelets.

32:46.214 --> 32:47.966
I really do have a lot of them.

32:48.091 --> 32:50.426
A casting director once told me
that my hands were mannish

32:50.510 --> 32:52.345
and gave me an absolute complex about it.

32:52.428 --> 32:54.806
So, now, I never go out
without a bangle or two

32:54.889 --> 32:55.974
to help cut the line, see?

32:56.057 --> 32:57.016
-Vivien...
-See?

32:57.809 --> 32:59.811
I think you're having a case
of the trembles again.

33:01.646 --> 33:02.981
When I get like this, I just...

33:03.940 --> 33:04.899
I can't stop.

33:09.779 --> 33:10.613
You and I...

33:12.115 --> 33:14.659
-have been through this before.
-Yes, yes.

33:16.369 --> 33:18.413
We just need to feed
the kitty a couple times.

33:18.496 --> 33:19.455
Oh, yes.

33:19.539 --> 33:21.207
[big band music plays]

33:29.716 --> 33:31.718
[all cheering]

33:46.232 --> 33:48.776
[Henry]All my life
I wanted to look like that.

33:49.652 --> 33:50.903
Work on my muscles.

33:50.987 --> 33:52.363
[chuckling]

33:52.613 --> 33:54.282
Charles Atlas kind of stuff.

33:55.616 --> 33:57.910
-Well, why didn't you?
-[Henry] Oh, I don't know.

33:57.994 --> 34:01.539
At some point I just knew
that I'd never be a beauty like that.

34:04.125 --> 34:06.878
I'd be the guy who helped
the beautiful people.

34:07.253 --> 34:08.296
Look at them.

34:08.379 --> 34:11.632
They look like chiseled Greek gods,
don't they, Dick?

34:15.344 --> 34:16.637
Henry, you're a vulgarian.

34:21.309 --> 34:22.143
Good night.

34:22.894 --> 34:26.147
Shouldn't you have left hours ago?
Something kept you here.

34:26.522 --> 34:27.356
What is that?

34:28.441 --> 34:29.776
What are you implying?

34:29.859 --> 34:32.612
You've always been such a mystery to me.

34:33.237 --> 34:35.615
Not a whiff of scandal about you.

34:35.698 --> 34:37.533
And yet, here you are,

34:37.617 --> 34:40.495
gazing in wonder at the statues,

34:41.329 --> 34:42.497
like in a museum.

34:46.626 --> 34:47.460
Fuck you.

34:49.045 --> 34:49.921
Excuse me.

34:52.215 --> 34:53.091
Oh, Rock.

34:53.591 --> 34:57.553
Rock Hudson, you remember Dick Samuels,
head of production at Ace Pictures?

34:57.804 --> 34:58.638
Hi, yeah.

34:59.305 --> 35:00.473
Always a pleasure.

35:00.556 --> 35:03.768
Rock was wondering if you and he
could go someplace private

35:03.851 --> 35:06.270
and talk about careers and such.

35:06.854 --> 35:10.108
Rock, why don't you take Dick
to that cottage back there? It's quiet.

35:12.026 --> 35:13.778
Why would I do that, Henry?

35:13.861 --> 35:15.279
Rock's just a young actor.

35:15.947 --> 35:17.073
New on the scene.

35:17.323 --> 35:19.784
You sure could use some career advice,
couldn't you, Rock?

35:20.952 --> 35:22.870
Yeah, is-- is that all right with you...

35:23.329 --> 35:24.330
Mr. Samuels?

35:29.544 --> 35:30.378
Sure.

35:30.628 --> 35:31.671
Why the hell not?

35:42.723 --> 35:44.433
[woman giggling]

35:55.236 --> 35:56.362
What are you doing?

35:56.445 --> 35:57.405
Nothing.

35:58.990 --> 36:01.450
Just admiring the furniture.

36:09.750 --> 36:11.002
It's all Billy Haines.

36:12.670 --> 36:14.213
-The decorator.
-Oh.

36:14.338 --> 36:15.923
Used to be a silent film star.

36:17.508 --> 36:18.843
He was on contract.

36:20.136 --> 36:22.638
But then Louis Mayer found out
which way he swung the bat

36:22.722 --> 36:25.850
and he told him, "Dump the fag boyfriend
or you're fired."

36:28.227 --> 36:29.312
You know what Billy said?

36:30.229 --> 36:32.356
He said, "Go fuck yourself. I quit."

36:33.232 --> 36:35.193
Then he started a decorating business.

36:36.027 --> 36:39.030
His first clients
were Joan Crawford and me.

36:39.989 --> 36:43.242
You don't hear a story like that
very often in this town, do you?

36:44.368 --> 36:47.455
Someone queer who stood up for himself...

36:48.623 --> 36:49.498
and won.

36:52.501 --> 36:55.254
Mr. Willson, I'm, uh... I'm Jack Castello.

36:55.338 --> 36:57.423
Miss Kincaid said I could use your help.

36:57.506 --> 37:00.343
I'm a new contract player at Ace Pictures,
but I don't have an agent

37:00.426 --> 37:01.385
or anything like that.

37:02.637 --> 37:03.846
[Henry sighs]

37:04.180 --> 37:05.640
So, we're talking business, huh?

37:06.349 --> 37:07.475
[Jack chuckles]

37:07.600 --> 37:09.352
Well, we can't talk business here.

37:10.770 --> 37:11.604
Let's take a walk.

37:12.521 --> 37:14.023
Oh, sure. Yeah.

37:46.055 --> 37:47.265
[Henry] Mmm!

37:49.183 --> 37:50.726
To Jack Castello.

37:53.020 --> 37:54.647
I actually like that name.

37:56.482 --> 37:58.150
That means "castle," doesn't it?

37:58.234 --> 37:59.193
[Jack] Mmm.

38:00.111 --> 38:02.780
Jack Castle. What, now, that's a name.

38:03.447 --> 38:05.700
All right. Let me get a good look at you.

38:09.578 --> 38:11.414
Mm-hmm. Okay.

38:13.624 --> 38:15.960
-Take the pants off.
-I beg your pardon?

38:16.043 --> 38:17.253
Are you hard of hearing?

38:17.336 --> 38:18.504
Take your pants off.

38:18.587 --> 38:20.423
I want to see what I'm working with.

38:41.736 --> 38:42.570
Not bad.

38:45.239 --> 38:46.407
You mind if I suck it?

38:51.746 --> 38:54.040
No, I'm sorry. I'm not...
I'm not doing this.

38:54.123 --> 38:55.583
Yeah you are, Jack.

38:57.543 --> 38:58.836
You should be flattered.

38:59.128 --> 39:01.088
I'm married. I got a wife at home.

39:01.172 --> 39:02.465
You think I give a fuck?

39:02.548 --> 39:04.717
I can't keep doing this to her, all right?

39:05.843 --> 39:07.553
You were my way out of this.

39:07.636 --> 39:10.639
I've been doing this.
I've been running around behind her back.

39:10.723 --> 39:13.601
-I've been lying to her.
-Why do you think you're doing that?

39:13.684 --> 39:14.894
'Cause I don't love her.

39:19.857 --> 39:20.733
I don't love her.

39:24.070 --> 39:25.071
I...

39:25.988 --> 39:29.408
Look, we met during the war, you know?
I was being shipped out. I was...

39:29.617 --> 39:31.744
I was terrified.
It felt like the world was ending,

39:31.827 --> 39:33.329
I wanted something to hold on to.

39:34.038 --> 39:36.248
I wanted somebody
I could pray to see again.

39:37.583 --> 39:39.418
It's different now.
Everything's different.

39:39.502 --> 39:40.711
I don't want the same things.

39:40.795 --> 39:42.004
What is it you do want?

39:42.088 --> 39:43.589
I wanna be somebody.

39:44.173 --> 39:46.217
That's why you need me, Jack.

39:47.343 --> 39:49.011
Fate has brought us together.

39:50.888 --> 39:51.972
Why do you...

39:52.723 --> 39:53.557
No.

39:55.643 --> 39:56.477
No.

39:58.312 --> 39:59.313
I'm not doing this.

40:00.064 --> 40:01.857
You're fucked without me, Jack.

40:01.982 --> 40:04.068
I can make that dream of yours come true.

40:04.151 --> 40:05.694
Don't you think I know that?

40:05.778 --> 40:08.906
But it ain't gonna mean anything
if this is what I do to get it!

40:09.156 --> 40:10.032
[snickers]

40:11.450 --> 40:12.326
[groans]

40:12.868 --> 40:13.702
Fuck you.

40:13.953 --> 40:16.288
-Fuck you, Jack. You're done.
-Pfft!

40:17.415 --> 40:19.208
It's over for you now. You're done.

40:25.965 --> 40:27.174
[Dick] Winnetka, huh?

40:27.800 --> 40:29.176
["Sometimes I'm Happy" playing]

40:29.260 --> 40:30.803
I've been to Winnetka, it's nice.

40:31.595 --> 40:34.515
[sighs] I-- I just can't believe
I said that about Vivien Leigh.

40:35.141 --> 40:38.352
Of course I've seen<i> Gone with the Wind,</i>
I just... I didn't recognize her.

40:38.436 --> 40:40.896
-She didn't look the same.
-Don't be so hard on yourself.

40:43.315 --> 40:46.444
<i>♪ Sometimes I'm happy ♪</i>

40:48.112 --> 40:51.615
<i>♪ Sometimes I'm blue... ♪</i>

40:53.117 --> 40:57.705
-[chuckles]
<i>-♪ My disposition ♪</i>

40:57.997 --> 41:01.792
<i>♪ Depends on you ♪</i>

41:03.043 --> 41:06.172
<i>♪ I never mind ♪</i>

41:06.922 --> 41:11.218
<i>♪ The rain from the sky ♪</i>

41:17.349 --> 41:21.103
[Dick sighs]

41:25.024 --> 41:26.317
Your heart is racing.

41:26.734 --> 41:28.903
I'm-- I'm just a little nervous,
that's all.

41:28.986 --> 41:30.446
[chuckles nervously]

41:59.850 --> 42:01.018
After we do this...

42:03.020 --> 42:05.314
we can talk about me getting
into a picture,

42:05.648 --> 42:06.899
right, Mr. Samuels?

42:15.407 --> 42:16.617
[exhales]

42:20.246 --> 42:21.163
[glass shatters]

42:21.622 --> 42:22.706
Put your clothes on.

42:23.749 --> 42:25.376
-I'm sorry?
-You heard me.

42:25.459 --> 42:27.503
I am not this person, and neither are you.

42:27.586 --> 42:29.463
Put your goddamn clothes on!

42:36.220 --> 42:37.638
I want to know your real name.

42:37.721 --> 42:39.640
The last thing I wanna do is upset you,
Mr.--

42:39.723 --> 42:42.059
Richard! My real name is Richard.

42:42.518 --> 42:46.188
Now tell me your real fucking name,
because it isn't Rock!

42:47.731 --> 42:48.566
Roy.

42:49.024 --> 42:50.150
Roy Fitzgerald.

42:52.319 --> 42:53.737
Henry came up with "Rock."

42:56.448 --> 42:59.326
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

43:00.452 --> 43:02.830
[breath shuddering] What have I done?

43:03.414 --> 43:04.540
[groans]

43:07.543 --> 43:09.670
All of my life, I've been a good man.

43:09.753 --> 43:11.088
I've been a company man.

43:12.131 --> 43:13.132
Which meant...

43:14.341 --> 43:16.802
that I couldn't be who I really was

43:16.885 --> 43:19.430
because then I would get fired, so...

43:20.139 --> 43:22.891
And the loneliness that comes along
with that, I just...

43:24.435 --> 43:27.438
I just accepted it, year after year.

43:27.521 --> 43:29.732
I've been pretending to be someone else.

43:29.815 --> 43:31.734
Just like you're pretending now.

43:31.817 --> 43:33.902
You play the part that
they've written for you...

43:34.778 --> 43:35.988
and then suddenly...

43:37.698 --> 43:38.699
suddenly, it's...

43:41.076 --> 43:42.202
[stammering] It's...

43:42.328 --> 43:43.537
it's just too late!

43:44.038 --> 43:44.872
You're lost.

43:45.331 --> 43:46.457
And...

43:46.540 --> 43:48.584
the person that you were, the... 

43:49.418 --> 43:51.170
the person that you wanted to be...

43:52.046 --> 43:53.172
is just swept...

43:54.298 --> 43:55.466
far out to sea

43:56.050 --> 43:57.968
and you're standing on the shore...

44:02.264 --> 44:03.682
You're watching the pers--

44:03.766 --> 44:05.517
You're watching the person go under,

44:05.601 --> 44:08.062
and there's nothing you can do about it.
It's just...

44:08.520 --> 44:09.563
It's just too late.

44:10.397 --> 44:12.858
And you hate yourself, because...

44:13.734 --> 44:17.488
you're the one responsible
for letting it happen.

44:19.490 --> 44:22.701
Because you wanted people in this town
to love you.

44:23.327 --> 44:25.496
To accept you.

44:31.377 --> 44:32.503
[Roy sniffles]

44:34.088 --> 44:35.964
Don't become me, Roy.

44:36.507 --> 44:37.549
[Roy] Okay.

44:41.095 --> 44:43.681
[sniffles]
Don't let Henry do anything to you.

44:44.098 --> 44:45.766
Whatever he's been doing...

44:46.767 --> 44:48.435
don't let him do it anymore.

44:50.479 --> 44:52.022
I shouldn't have come in here.

44:52.106 --> 44:52.940
I'm sorry.

44:53.399 --> 44:55.609
Nothing happened here tonight,
Mr. Samuels,

44:56.652 --> 44:58.654
except you being a good man. That's all.

44:59.655 --> 45:02.032
You're about the first good man
I've met in Hollywood.

45:03.325 --> 45:04.660
Now, don't you fret, okay?

45:05.411 --> 45:06.537
Let's get you a taxi.

45:07.830 --> 45:08.956
[Archie] Ah!

45:09.039 --> 45:12.000
-Oh, yes, yes, yes.
-[Noel chuckling]

45:12.334 --> 45:15.421
[Archie chuckling] Oh, yep. Yes.

45:17.589 --> 45:19.425
Get your hands off of him, please.

45:20.092 --> 45:21.844
-Rock.
-I beg your pardon.

45:21.927 --> 45:23.595
Hands off. That's my boyfriend.

45:26.640 --> 45:28.767
Well, I didn't know you were taken.

45:30.018 --> 45:32.271
If I had, perhaps I wouldn't have wasted
my evening.

45:34.732 --> 45:36.775
Rock, you can't do that.

45:37.151 --> 45:38.402
I don't belong to you.

45:38.902 --> 45:40.112
Well, I belong to you.

45:42.489 --> 45:43.407
Dance with me.

45:43.782 --> 45:45.701
-Folks are gonna see--
-I don't care.

45:46.702 --> 45:47.995
I don't care about that.

45:49.121 --> 45:50.122
I care about you.

45:52.541 --> 45:53.375
I love you.

45:55.085 --> 45:57.087
No one's ever said that to me before.

45:58.547 --> 46:00.549
Don't say anything, Archie.

46:01.049 --> 46:02.092
Just dance with me.

46:17.107 --> 46:19.651
[door opens and closes]

46:19.777 --> 46:21.278
[Raymond sighs]

46:21.361 --> 46:23.906
-[Camille] How was the party?
-Oh, George Cukor...

46:23.989 --> 46:25.908
I tell you, what an absolute gem.

46:26.408 --> 46:27.910
I talked to him about <i>Peg.</i>

46:27.993 --> 46:30.871
I told him about the look
that I was going for...

46:30.954 --> 46:34.249
Raymond, I've been thinking,
and I owe you an apology.

46:34.833 --> 46:38.545
I shouldn't be manipulating you
to put me into your movie.

46:38.629 --> 46:41.048
-Forget that I even--
-What are you talking about?

46:41.131 --> 46:42.299
Stop it. Please.

46:42.716 --> 46:45.344
Come on. That's-- that's just nonsense.

46:46.011 --> 46:48.680
Camille, last night's conversation
got me thinking.

46:49.932 --> 46:50.974
Made me examine...

46:51.934 --> 46:53.060
what we are.

46:53.727 --> 46:54.603
And...

46:55.354 --> 46:56.730
Honey, I'm not just...

46:57.397 --> 46:59.608
sleeping with an actress.

47:01.443 --> 47:04.238
I'm head over heels in love with her.

47:04.822 --> 47:05.864
[Camille] Mm-hmm.

47:05.948 --> 47:07.908
And I hope to marry her one day.

47:10.077 --> 47:11.411
And I so,

47:12.412 --> 47:14.581
to my very core, believe in her.

47:14.706 --> 47:15.874
That's why I think...

47:16.667 --> 47:17.501
you...

47:18.544 --> 47:19.962
need to be in that spotlight.

47:20.379 --> 47:22.381
Your name needs to be on that marquee.

47:22.464 --> 47:24.550
I want you to be the star of <i>Meg.</i>

47:26.927 --> 47:27.803
Really?

47:27.886 --> 47:29.096
You're a star, Camille.

47:29.179 --> 47:32.182
You're a star,
and of course you're right for this part.

47:33.141 --> 47:35.602
I'm just so embarrassed
it took me this long to see it.

47:35.686 --> 47:36.520
And I'm sorry.

47:37.312 --> 47:38.856
I'm going to get you that screen test,

47:38.939 --> 47:41.149
I don't care how hard I gotta fight
to make it happen.

47:41.859 --> 47:43.318
[both chuckling]

47:52.619 --> 47:54.329
[Henrietta] How was the night shoot?

47:57.875 --> 47:58.792
It was good.

47:59.543 --> 48:00.669
It was good, um...

48:03.463 --> 48:05.340
Went longer than I thought, you know?
But...

48:06.466 --> 48:07.885
we got everything.

48:09.928 --> 48:11.221
I thought you'd be asleep.

48:12.431 --> 48:16.101
I tried, but these two decided
to have a boxing match.

48:35.454 --> 48:36.914
[crying] I'm sorry, Hen.

48:37.497 --> 48:38.457
For what?

48:38.540 --> 48:40.208
You deserve so much better, and...

48:40.292 --> 48:43.003
I'm sorry, and I promise
I'm gonna do better.

48:45.422 --> 48:46.256
Come on.

48:46.632 --> 48:47.716
[Jack sniffles]

48:52.763 --> 48:53.722
I love you.

48:55.057 --> 48:56.516
You know that, right?

48:57.142 --> 48:58.185
[sniffles]

49:05.609 --> 49:06.944
Let's go to bed.

49:22.918 --> 49:25.170
[Dick]
So your mother is from the Philippines.

49:25.253 --> 49:27.047
Why didn't you mention this before?

49:27.130 --> 49:31.468
I didn't want to risk
being put in a category, so I-- I hid.

49:33.929 --> 49:35.639
I was ashamed of who I was.

49:35.722 --> 49:39.434
But I'm tired of playing it safe.
I want to be different.

49:39.518 --> 49:42.396
I want to be who I am
and I want to start taking risks.

49:43.814 --> 49:47.401
Camille Washington is the best actress
for this role, and you know it.

49:47.484 --> 49:49.486
I insist that she be given a screen test.

49:50.612 --> 49:52.280
If that doesn't happen, then...

49:54.199 --> 49:55.617
then I don't direct the picture.

49:55.742 --> 49:56.785
It's as simple as that.

49:59.204 --> 50:00.664
Thank you for your time.

50:06.920 --> 50:08.296
[door opens and closes]

50:08.422 --> 50:09.840
Well, he's right, you know.

50:10.841 --> 50:12.092
Of course he's right.

50:12.843 --> 50:13.969
[Ellen exhales]

50:15.721 --> 50:17.305
Which is why we're going to do it.

50:18.682 --> 50:19.975
[Ellen chuckling] My God.

50:20.058 --> 50:21.852
What the hell will Ace say?

50:21.935 --> 50:24.021
-This could get us fired.
-Oh, please.

50:24.354 --> 50:26.732
I'd love to see him try to run this studio
on his own.

50:26.815 --> 50:28.567
That imbecile can barely read.

50:29.067 --> 50:30.777
I didn't fight for Anna May Wong.

50:31.194 --> 50:33.155
I didn't fight for a lot of people.

50:35.532 --> 50:36.658
I want to fight again.

50:36.742 --> 50:40.245
And Ace can't stop us
if you and I are willing to fight.

50:40.328 --> 50:41.788
Richard, I could kiss you.

50:41.872 --> 50:43.749
This is exactly
what this studio needs right now.

50:43.832 --> 50:46.710
Something no one saw coming,
something new, something fresh.

50:47.878 --> 50:49.421
Let's test her and see how she does.

50:49.504 --> 50:51.798
God, I love it when you talk like a mogul.

50:52.132 --> 50:53.508
It's almost convincing.

50:53.592 --> 50:55.385
Watch it, Kincaid, or I'll fire you.

50:55.469 --> 50:56.720
[kisses, laughing]

50:56.803 --> 50:58.055
You wouldn't dare.

50:58.764 --> 51:02.100
Rock, I wanted to apologize
about last night.

51:02.184 --> 51:05.187
I had too much to drink
and I crossed a line.

51:05.270 --> 51:07.314
I should never have
sent you off with Dick

51:07.397 --> 51:08.648
and I'm sorry.

51:08.732 --> 51:11.359
That's all right, Mr. Willson.
Nothing happened.

51:11.443 --> 51:12.277
Really?

51:13.278 --> 51:14.112
Shit.

51:14.946 --> 51:15.947
Kinda wish it had.

51:16.406 --> 51:17.574
Could've used it against him.

51:17.657 --> 51:18.658
Anyway...

51:19.493 --> 51:20.660
uh...

51:21.453 --> 51:24.998
Oh, as for <i>Peg,</i>
I think I can get you this part.

51:25.332 --> 51:29.669
Your screen test has to go well,
but I'm in Dick's ear about it,

51:29.753 --> 51:33.090
and Ace Amberg's wife, Avis?
She's a close friend of mine.

51:33.465 --> 51:35.884
Mr. Willson, I don't--
I don't know what to say.

51:35.967 --> 51:37.302
Let me say something, then.

51:38.345 --> 51:40.472
You bring out something in me, Rock.

51:41.056 --> 51:43.308
Something I haven't felt in a long time.

51:43.683 --> 51:44.726
You're something...

51:47.145 --> 51:49.439
You're some-<i>one</i> I can believe in.

51:49.523 --> 51:52.317
Someone who needs me
to be the best I can be.

51:52.400 --> 51:54.444
It's been a long time since I felt that.

51:55.237 --> 51:56.863
It was a long time ago now.

51:56.947 --> 51:58.740
Even feels longer than it was.

52:00.158 --> 52:01.284
I met somebody.

52:02.702 --> 52:05.580
Trent was his name. Trent Durkin.

52:05.664 --> 52:07.582
But everybody called him Junior.

52:08.250 --> 52:10.085
He was so good-looking.

52:11.378 --> 52:13.713
I couldn't believe he had eyes for me.

52:14.381 --> 52:16.550
And when he smiled, it just--

52:17.300 --> 52:19.427
[chuckling] ...it just lit up a room.

52:20.053 --> 52:21.930
You couldn't take your eyes off him.

52:24.391 --> 52:26.059
And he cared for me.

52:28.562 --> 52:30.272
I was a nothing then, but...

52:31.815 --> 52:34.484
he thought I was somebody, he really did.

52:36.403 --> 52:39.447
And that is something
I never thought would happen.

52:39.698 --> 52:41.324
I thought my life would come and go

52:41.408 --> 52:43.410
and I would never know
what that felt like.

52:44.661 --> 52:45.829
He and I...

52:46.329 --> 52:48.081
[sighs] ...we were inseparable.

52:51.126 --> 52:52.502
We lived together.

52:54.713 --> 52:56.798
Junior wanted to be a movie star.

52:57.757 --> 53:00.719
And I wanted to be the one
who made that happen.

53:06.433 --> 53:07.475
One night...

53:09.311 --> 53:11.271
he was killed in a car crash.

53:15.025 --> 53:16.443
I cradled his body.

53:18.653 --> 53:19.863
And I kissed him.

53:21.948 --> 53:23.575
And I told him I loved him.

53:25.410 --> 53:27.704
[breath shuddering]
But he was already gone.

53:30.123 --> 53:31.917
Something in me just broke.

53:33.293 --> 53:34.711
You know what I mean?

53:34.836 --> 53:37.505
I couldn't even remember
what it felt like to love him.

53:43.261 --> 53:45.180
And there's something about you, Rock.

53:47.641 --> 53:50.018
It makes me remember what that felt like.

53:51.603 --> 53:52.646
To have Junior.

53:54.981 --> 53:56.358
And I know you're not him.

53:57.734 --> 53:59.527
You're nothing like him, actually, but...

54:00.654 --> 54:01.821
meeting you...

54:03.031 --> 54:05.242
My life has a purpose again.

54:06.034 --> 54:07.702
I have a passion again.

54:08.536 --> 54:10.789
You are my passion, Rock Hudson.

54:10.872 --> 54:13.124
I'd kill for you, kid,
and I ain't foolin'.

54:15.794 --> 54:18.088
I'm gonna make you
the biggest star in the world.

54:22.717 --> 54:24.678
Um, Mr. Willson, I don't know what to...

54:25.595 --> 54:27.305
Well, I'm speechless.

54:27.389 --> 54:29.766
Make yourself useful and grab me a tissue,
you big galoot.

54:29.849 --> 54:31.226
I'm crying like a baby over here.

54:38.441 --> 54:40.193
[pours drink]

54:44.656 --> 54:47.575
Mmm! Oh, that's much better. Thank you.

54:48.326 --> 54:49.202
So...

54:49.869 --> 54:51.788
[sniffles] So, the screen test.

54:52.747 --> 54:54.874
-Friday morning.
-What, this... this Friday?

54:54.958 --> 54:55.792
Yeah.

54:56.793 --> 54:59.796
Oh, thank you, Mr. Willson.
I can't thank you enough.

54:59.921 --> 55:02.257
Well, do you remember what I said
about actors?

55:02.340 --> 55:05.343
How they're garbage, can't be trusted?
You can't be friends with them?

55:05.427 --> 55:06.594
I didn't mean that.

55:07.554 --> 55:11.641
God, you're new in town,
you could use some friends, probably.

55:12.726 --> 55:13.601
Yeah.

55:13.685 --> 55:15.228
Yeah, that'd be nice.

55:15.312 --> 55:17.105
-Oh.
-[Roy chuckles]

55:17.314 --> 55:19.274
Good, I was hoping you'd say that.

55:19.858 --> 55:20.692
Come here.

55:23.111 --> 55:25.530
I got a couple of new clients
I want you to meet.

55:27.615 --> 55:30.618
Rock, this is Rory Calhoun
and Tank Meyers.

55:30.702 --> 55:33.455
Boys, this is the fella
I was telling you about.

55:33.538 --> 55:34.372
Hiya, Rock.

55:34.831 --> 55:35.790
Nice to meet you.

55:36.166 --> 55:37.000
[Roy] Hi.

55:37.083 --> 55:38.418
-How you doing?
-Uh, good.

55:39.210 --> 55:41.755
Uh, H-- Henry, what's going on here?

55:41.838 --> 55:45.050
Nothing's happening.
These are just your new friends.

55:45.133 --> 55:47.677
You're gonna sit over there on the bed

55:47.761 --> 55:52.182
and I'm gonna watch while
the three of you, you get acquainted.

55:53.391 --> 55:55.602
So what were you fellas talking about?

55:56.019 --> 55:58.313
Um... football.

55:58.396 --> 56:02.150
Oh, yeah? Got a couple
of real professors here, right?

56:07.822 --> 56:09.824
[big band music playing]
